  * Cached RSS XML files to avoid checking every run
  * GUI
  * Download rate limiting - on a per-feed basis
  * Email notifications
  * Transcoding support
  * Back-end database tracking, logging and statistics
  * Robust handling of default values for incomplete configs (https://bitbucket.org/daybologic/dlpodget.defaults)
  * Non-RSS feeds
  * User-defined download order
  * Full documentation / PoD
  * Graceful timeout handling
  * OOP re-write
  * Java re-write?
  * Archived feed support (frozen feeds)
  * Quiet mode (-q) for use from crontab
  * Unit test using Dummy::LWP::UserAgent
  * Optional rotation of old downloaded streams, requested by https://bitbucket.org/Aggamemnon

The following modules should be broken out from the monolithic script:
  * LEGACY:

